{"parse":{"title":"lemon","pageid":4844,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"{{also|Lemon|lemön}}\n==English==\n{{wp|[[+|+ (fruit and tree)]]}}\n{{wp|+ (color)}}\n{{wikispecies|Citrus limon}}\n{{wp|+ (geometry)}}\n[[Image:Lemon.jpg|thumb|250px|A whole and a cut '''lemon'''.]]\n[[image:Lemon tree Berkeley.JPG|thumb|250px|A '''lemon''' tree.]]\n[[image:Lemon_(geometry).png|thumb|250px|A '''lemon''' shape in geometry.]]\n\n===Etymology===\n{{etymon|en|id=lemon fruit|:inh|enm:lymon<id:lemon fruit mid en>|tree=1}}\n{{inh+|en|enm|lymon}}, from {{der|en|fro|lymon||citrus}}, from {{der|en|ar|لَيْمُون}} or {{der|en|fa|لیمون|tr=limon}}, from {{der|en|fa|لیمو|tr=limu}}, from {{der|en|sa|निम्बू||lime}}, ultimately from {{der|en|poz-pro|*limaw}} or {{der|en|mun||lime}}.<ref>{{R:Etymonline|lemon}}</ref> {{doublet|en|lime}}.\n\nThe fandom sense is named after the erotic anime series ''{{w|Cream Lemon}}''.<ref>Maria Lindgren Leavenworth & Malin Isaksson, ''Fanged Fan Fiction: Variations on Twilight, True Blood and The Vampire Diaries'', [https://books.google.com/books?id=4foQAAAAQBAJ&pg=PA118&dq=%22cream+lemon%22 page 118]</ref>\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{enPR|lĕm'ən}}, {{IPA|en|/ˈlɛmən/|/ˈlɛmɪn/}}\n** {{audio|en|En-uk-lemon.ogg|a=London}}\n** {{audio|en|LL-Q1860 (eng)-Simplificationalizer-lemon.wav|a=New Jersey}}\n** {{IPA|en|/ˈlɪmɪn/|a=pin-pen}}\n* {{rhymes|en|ɛmən|ɛmɪn|s=2}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{en-noun|#}}\n\n# {{senseid|en|Q1093742}}A yellowish [[citrus]] [[fruit]].\n#* {{quote-book|en|title=The Kitchin-Phyſician; Or, a Guide for Good-Housewives in Maintaining Their Families in Health. {{...}}|passage=The juice of '''Lemmons''' killeth Warts, but better the water of the ſame juice, diſtilled through a glaſs.|year=1680|author=T. K.|page=14|section=How to take away Warts off the Face or Hands|pageurl=https://www.google.com.au/books/edition/The_Kitchin_Physician_Or_a_Guide_for_Goo/efpmAAAAcAAJ?hl=en&gbpv=1&pg=PA14|url=https://www.google.com.au/books/edition/The_Kitchin_Physician_Or_a_Guide_for_Goo/efpmAAAAcAAJ?hl=en&gbpv=0}}\n# A semitropical [[evergreen]] [[tree]], {{taxfmt|Citrus limon|species}}, that bears such fruits.\n# A more or less bright [[shade]] of [[yellow]] associated with lemon fruits.\n#: {{color panel|lemon flesh|2=FADA5E}}\n#: {{color panel|lemon rind|2=FDE910}}\n# {{lb|en|uncountable|rare}} [[lemon juice|Lemon juice]].\n#* {{RQ:Eliza Smith Compleat Housewife|edition=8th|chapter=Sauce for Boiled Turkey or Chickens|page=99|passage=[J]uſt at the laſt ſcald four or five ſpoonfuls of thick new cream, with a few drops of '''lemon''' or vinegar, muſhrooms pickled do well, {{...}}}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1887|author=Sarah A. Grier|chapter=VIII|title=A Few Hints about Cooking, with Remarks on Many Other Subjects|location=Boston, Mass.|publisher=Wright & Potter Printing Company,{{nb...|18 Post Office Square.}}|page=111|pageurl=https://books.google.com/books?id=ztwqAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA111|oclc=3283113|passage=[S]tir into this, after taking from the fire, two ounces of butter cut into little bits, putting in one piece at a time, and squeeze a few drops of '''lemon''' in this sauce.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1989|author=David Johnston|chapter=Notes|mainauthor=w:Federico García Lorca|tlr=David Johnston|title=w:Blood Wedding|location=London|publisher=w:Hodder & Stoughton|year_published=1998 (17th impression)|section=note 14|page=109|pageurl=https://archive.org/details/bloodwedding0000garc/page/109/mode/1up|isbn=0 340 51269 5|passage=The fact that he is drinking '''lemon''' is, therefore, an image of the bitterness of his life.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=2018|author=Jehad O. Halabi|quotee=Muna|chapter=Case Study: Traditional Health Beliefs of Arabic Culture During Pregnancy|editors=Marilyn “Marty” Douglas; Dula Pacquiao; Larry Purnell|title=Global Applications of Culturally Competent Health Care: Guidelines for Practice|location=Cham|publisher=[[w:Springer Nature|Springer International Publishing AG]]|section=part II (Guideline: Education and Training)|page=79|pageurl=https://books.google.com/books?id=TdNiDwAAQBAJ&pg=PA79|column=1|isbn=978-3-319-69331-6|passage=She should stay in bed for 40 days and should avoid getting close to her husband till the end of 40 days, not taking a shower, not drinking '''lemon''', and not letting anybody enter her room while she has her menses because this will affect her milk.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=2018|author=Sally Olivia Kim|chapter=Vanilla Lemon Latte|chapterurl=https://books.google.com/books?id=5QJsDwAAQBAJ&pg=PT155|title=The Collagen Glow: A Guide to Ingestible Skincare|location=New York, N.Y.|publisher=[[w:The Countryman Press|W. W. Norton & Company]]|section=“Hot and Cold Drinks” section|isbn=978-1-68268-334-7|passage=Drinking '''lemon''' is known to aid with digestion, as it contains limonene, compounds that can assist with weight loss and fighting inflammation!}}\n# A [[lemon shark]] ({{taxfmt|Negaprion brevirostris|species}}).\n# {{lb|en|slang}} A [[defective]] or [[inadequate]] item or individual.\n#: {{ux|en|He didn’t realise until he’d paid for it that the car was a '''lemon'''.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1951|author=Herman Wouk|title=The Caine Mutiny|chapter=20|page=243|passage=“{{...}}the Navy's supposed to give me a ship that goes, and a captain that fights—— That's what all this muck is for, isn't it?” <br> “Look, it's an old story by now. We're stuck with a '''lemon'''. Misfortune of war.{{...}}”}}\n# {{lb|en|[[Cockney rhyming slang]]|shortened from “lemon flavour”}} [[favor|Favor]].\n#: {{ux|en|A thousand quid for that motor? Do me a '''lemon'''! I could get it for half that.}}\n# {{lb|en|dated|fandom}} A piece of [[fanfiction]] involving [[explicit]] sex.\n#* {{quote-newsgroup|en|date=18 April 1997|author=Neko|title=[Dominion][FanFic][Lemon] A Typical Night at the Station |url=https://groups.google.com/forum/#!original/rec.arts.anime.creative/JpLlph5L2zM/sOGJPVZ2aAIJ|newsgroup=rec.arts.anime.creative |passage=I'd really like to know what people think of this and whether I should carry on writing '''lemons''' or go and hide under a rock somewhere.}}\n#* {{quote-newsgroup|en|date=30 May 2000|author=Ian Blakeman|title=[Eva][FanFic][Lemon] A day at Misatos appartment{{sic}}|url=https://groups.google.com/forum/#!original/rec.arts.anime.creative/GUzvPm57pMQ/JuhoMRQDJ2cJ|newsgroup=rec.arts.anime.creative |passage=WARNING: This story is a '''lemon''' and must be viewed with great care. If you are either under the age of 18, think graphic sex is discussing{{sic}} or you know what my writing is like you should turn away now.}}\n#* {{quote-newsgroup|en|date=10 November 2002|author=Goku Girl|title=[DBZ][FanFic][Yaoi] Saiya-jin no Suto-ri Ichi (part one)|url=https://groups.google.com/forum/#!original/rec.arts.anime.creative/Te9DFhiaVWE/eM3molZiVHcJ|newsgroup=rec.arts.anime.creative |passage=This won't be a '''lemon''' simply because I can't see myself writing anything like that.}}\n# {{senseid|en|geometry}} {{lb|en|geometry}} The [[surface of revolution]] of a [[circular arc]] of angle less than 180° rotated about the [[straight line]] passing through the arc’s two [[endpoint]]s.\n#: {{cot|en|{{l|en|apple|id=geometry}}}}\n\n====Alternative forms====\n* {{l|en|limon}} {{qual|obsolete}}\n\n====Synonyms====\n* {{sense|defective item}} {{l|en|bomb}}\n* {{sense|erotic fanfiction}} {{l|en|PWP}}, {{l|en|smutfic}}\n* {{sense|color}} {{l|en|lemon yellow}}\n\n====Hypernyms====\n* [[Thesaurus:fruit|fruit]]\n** {{l|en|citrus}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col4|en\n|acid of lemon\n|bitter lemon|[[bush lemon]] ({{taxlink|Citrus jhambiri|species}})\n|Canton lemon\n|do me a lemon\n|easy peasy lemon squeezy\n|[[Ichang lemon]] ({{taxlink|Citrus cavaleriei|species}} × {{taxfmt|Citrus maxima|species}})\n|lemandarin\n|lemonade|lemonaise|lemonal|[[lemon ant]] ({{taxlink|Myrmelachista schumanni|species}})|lemonary\n|[[lemon balm]] ({{taxfmt|Melissa officinalis|species}})|lemon bar|[[lemon basil]] ({{taxlink|Ocimum × citriodorum|nothospecies}})|{{vern|lemon beebrush}} ({{taxlink|Aloysia citrodora|species}})|[[lemon-bellied flycatcher]] ({{taxlink|Microeca flavigaster|species}})|[[lemon-bellied flyrobin]] ({{taxlink|Microeca flavigaster|species}})|lemon-belly|lemon martini\n|lemon cheese|lemon chicken|lemon chiffon|lemon chiffon pie|[[lemon clover]] ({{taxfmt|Oxalis stricta|species}})|lemon curd\n|{{vern|lemon daylily}} ({{taxlink|Hemerocallis lilioasphodelus|species}} var., syn. {{taxlink|Hemerocallis flava|species}} var.)|lemon drop\n|[[lemon eucalyptus]] ({{taxfmt|Corymbia citriodora|species}})\n|lemonfish\n|[[lemon geranium]] ({{taxlink|Pelargonium crispum|species}})|[[lemongrass]], {{vern|lemon grass}} ({{taxfmt|Cymbopogon|genus}} spp., esp. {{taxfmt|Cymbopogon citratus|species}})\n|lemon heaven\n|lemonime|lemonish|lemonize\n|lemon juice\n|lemon laundering|lemon law|lemonless|lemonlike|[[lemon lily]] ({{taxlink|Hemerocallis lilioasphodelus|species}} var., syn. {{taxlink|Hemerocallis flava|species}} var.)|lemon-lime,lemon lime\n|lemon meringue|lemon meringue pie|lemon mint|[[lemon myrtle]] ({{taxlink|Backhousia citriodora|species}})\n|lemon pepper|lemon plait\n|lemonquat\n|lemonrita\n|[[lemon shark]] ({{taxlink|Microstomus kitt|species}})|lemon socialism|lemon soda|[[lemon sole]] ({{taxlink|Microstomus kitt|species}})|lemon square|lemon squash|lemon squeezer,lemon-squeezer\n|lemon tea|[[lemon thyme]] (''{{ll|mul|Thymus}}'' spp.)|lemontini|Lemon Tree\n|[[lemon verbena]], {{vern|lemon vervain}} ({{taxlink|Aloysia citrodora|species}})\n|lemon water|lemonweed|lemonwood\n|lemony|lemon yellow\n|[[Meyer lemon]] ({{taxlink|Citrus × meyeri|nothospecies}})\n|oil of lemon eucalyptus\n|Philippine lemon|[[ponderosa lemon]] ({{taxlink|Citrus × pyriformis|nothospecies}})\n|[[rough lemon]] ({{taxlink|Citrus jhambiri|species}})\n|salt of lemon|[[sea lemon]] ({{taxfmt|Dorididae|family}} spp.; {{taxfmt|Ximenia americana|species}})|sharptooth lemon shark|sicklefin lemon shark|sit there like a lemon|stand there like a lemon|suck a lemon|[[sweet lemon]] ({{taxfmt|Citrus|genus}} hybrids)\n|tangemon\n|Volkamer lemon\n|[[water lemon]] ({{taxlink|Passiflora laurifolia|species}})\n}}\n\n====Related terms====\n* {{l|en|limonene}}\n\n====Descendants====\n* {{desc|csb|lemòna|bor=1|qq=Canada, United States}}\n\n====Translations====\n{{trans-top|citrus fruit}}\n* Afrikaans: {{t+|af|suurlemoen}}\n* Albanian: {{t+|sq|limon|m}}\n* Arabic: {{t|ar|لَيْمُون|m}}\n*: Egyptian Arabic: {{t|arz|لمون|m|tr=lamūn}}\n*: Hijazi Arabic: {{t|acw|ليمون|m|tr=laymūn}}\n*: Moroccan Arabic: {{t|ary|حامض|tr=ḥāmeḍ}} {{qualifier|collective}}, {{t|ary|حامضة|tr=ḥāmḍa}} {{qualifier|singulative}}\n*: North Levantine Arabic: {{t|apc|حامُض|m|tr=ḥāmoḍ}} {{q|Lebanon}}\n*: North Levantine Arabic: {{t|apc|ليمون|m|tr=lēmūn}} {{q|Syria}}\n*: South Levantine Arabic: {{t|ajp|لمون|m|tr=lamūn, laymūn, lemūn}}, {{t|ajp|حامض|m|tr=ḥāmeḍ}} {{qualifier|Galilee}}\n* Aramaic:\n*: Assyrian Neo-Aramaic: {{t|aii|ܠܝܼܡܘܼܢܵܐ|tr=līmuna|m}}\n* Armenian: {{t+|hy|կիտրոն}}, {{t+|hy|լիմոն}}\n* Assamese: {{t|as|নেমু}}, {{t|as|নেমু-টেঙা}}\n* Asturian: {{t+|ast|llimón|m}}\n* Azerbaijani: {{t+|az|limon}}\n*: South Azerbaijani: {{t|az|لیمو|tr=limu/lumu}}\n* Basque: {{t+|eu|limoi}}\n* Belarusian: {{t|be|лімо́н|m}}, {{t|be|цытры́на|f}}\n* Bengali: {{t+|bn|লেবু}}\n* Bhojpuri: {{t|bho|नींबू}}\n* Breton: {{t|br|sitron|m}}, {{t|br|sitronoù|p}}, {{t|br|suraval|m}}, {{qualifier|1}} {{t|br|suravaloù|p}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|лимо́н|m}}\n* Burmese: {{t+|my|ရှောက်}}, {{t+|my|သံပရို}}\n* Catalan: {{t+|ca|llimona|f}}\n* Cherokee: {{t|chr|ᎵᎹᏂ}}\n* Chichewa: {{t|ny|ndimu}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Cantonese: {{t|yue|檸檬|tr=ning4 mung1}}\n*: Hakka: {{t|hak|檸檬|tr=lê-móng}}\n*: Hokkien: {{t+|nan-hbl|檸檬|tr=lê-bóng}}\n*: Mandarin: {{t+|cmn|檸檬|tr=níngméng}}\n* Cornish: {{t|kw|lymmaval}}\n* Czech: {{t+|cs|citrón|m}}, {{t+|cs|citron}}\n* Danish: {{t+|da|citron|c}}\n* Dhivehi: {{t|dv|ގޮމަށި}}\n* Dutch: {{t+|nl|citroen|f}}\n* Dzongkha: {{t|dz|ཧུམ་ཅུང}}\n* East Frisian Low German: {{t|frs|tsiitrôon|f}}, {{