 (scent)\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|having the colour/color of lemons}}\n* Danish: {{t|da|citrongul}}\n* Dutch: {{t+|nl|citroengele}}\n* Estonian: {{t|et|sidrunkollane}}\n* Finnish: {{t|fi|sitruunankeltainen}}, {{t|fi|[[sitruuna|sitruunan]] [[värinen]]}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|jaune citron}}\n* German: {{t+|de|zitronengelb}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|λεμονί}}\n* Latvian: {{t|lv|citrondzeltens}}\n* Pannonian Rusyn: {{t|rsk|лимункови}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|cytrynowy|m}}\n* Portuguese: {{t|pt|limonado}}, {{t|pt|limoado}}, {{t|pt|alimonado}}, {{t|pt|alimoado}}\n* Romanian: {{t|ro|galben-verziu}}\n* Spanish: {{t|es|limonado}}, {{t+|es|limón}}\n* Swahili: {{t+|sw|ndimu}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|citrongul}}\n* Vietnamese: {{t|vi|màu chanh}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===Verb===\n{{en-verb}}\n\n# {{lb|en|transitive}} To flavour with lemon.\n#: {{ux|en|You can start the vegetables cooking while you are '''lemoning''' the fish.}}\n\n===See also===\n* {{l|en|citrine}}\n* {{l|en|citron}}\n* {{l|en|citronella}}\n* {{l|en|melissa}}\n* {{l|en|fever grass}}\n* [[Appendix:Colors]]\n\n===References===\n<references/>\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|en|a=elmno|Menlo|Monel|melon|nmole}}\n\n{{C|en|Citrus subfamily plants|Erotic literature|Fan fiction|Fruits|Yellows}}\n\n==Esperanto==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{eo-pr|a=LL-Q143 (epo)-TranqyPoo-lemon.wav}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{eo-head}}\n\n# {{eo-form of|lem|on}}\n\n==Welsh==\n{{wp|cy:}}\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{l|cy|lemwn}}\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{der|cy|en|lemon}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|cy|/ˈlɛmɔn/}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{cy-noun|m|lemonau}}\n\n# [[#English|lemon]]\n\n====Related terms====\n* {{l|cy|lemonêd||lemonade}}\n\n{{topics|cy|Fruits}}\n\n==Western Huasteca Nahuatl==\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|nhw|noun}}\n\n# [[#English|lemon]].\n\n{{C|nhw|Fruits}}"}}